</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-20C4C343-9487-4E59-868B-B02740EEC1F5" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Dr. Account Receivables
Cr. Revenue (Sales)
Cr. Taxes (if applicable)
</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-B95388DE-6873-41C2-A712-5D81EBFFF519" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>AR entry will be technically cleared as per standard SAP functionality
</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-0B929BD6-47BE-4803-A01F-22343319E8C6" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="" fontFamily="" fontSize="" italic="true" ref="text-left"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="" fontFamily="" fontSize="" italic="true" ref="text-right"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Based on S/4 Workflow Decision Matrix (including Cancellation Window
And BU approval if NCNR order 

Business Rules Matrix (Examples)​
1) If order is yet to be confirmed, then the order can be cancelled therefore will not need to follow NCNR ​
2) If the material is EOL, no cancellation/pushout allowed.​
3) Dispatched/GI orders should not be allowed for cancellation.​
</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-DFBF0140-2C51-4D13-99E8-5DDCD29FF391" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
